        <property propertyId="6bc8ac5e-cc4c-45fb-93dc-53c0e45091df" amount="4.488" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e">
          <name xml:lang="en">energy content</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">{3,3,1,3,5} The gross energy content of Sweet Corn is 18.7MJ/kg on a dry matter basis, 87.2% dry matter as fed for North American Sweet Corn (Feedipedia - Maize 2017). At the harvest moisture content of 76.% (Neibauer, J. and Maynard, E. 2012), the energy content of Sweet Corn is 4.5MJ/kg product weight
Source(s): 
Heuzé V., Tran G., Lebas F. (2017) Maize grain. Feedipedia, a programme by INRAE, CIRAD, AFZ and FAO. https://www.feedipedia.org/node/556 Last updated on September 7, 2017, 14:29. ; Neibauer, J. and Maynard, E. (2012) Sweetcorn Produce Quality and Safety. Purdue University. https://www.hort.purdue.edu/prod_quality/commodities/sweetcorn.html</comment>
        </property>
        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.550470435" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The price per kg of sweetcorn is considered for the years 2016-2021 for the state of Florida in the US. The values were retrieved in $/CWT [1] and converted into $/kg. References: [1] US Department of Agriculture (NASS), Quickstat, TabLe "SWEETCORN - PRICE RECEIVED, MEASURED IN $ / CWT", accessed on 25.08.2023, available at: https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/
The prices were converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.AUD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
