      <intermediateExchange id="de18ffba-e8fa-5698-b866-b4cdff0f066f" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.0031102097695109" intermediateExchangeId="aa0f0057-073d-55b7-918d-e4d6bed420f3" activityLinkId="8b1ae3b7-9789-549f-a1de-f75268c8a4b0">
        <name xml:lang="en">NPK (15-15-15) fertiliser</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">3.11E-3 kg NPK (15-15-15) fertiliser/kg Sweet Corn 
Quantities of specific fertiliser are calculated based on US fertiliser market share and nutrient compositions from IFA data to meet total nutrient demand N-P-K-S: 102.52--8.55--0.35--2.97 kg/ha  (USDA NASS data for 2018), over reported cropped area of specified crop (conventional tillage): quantity of N applied to treated acres times percent of planted sweetcorn acres (USDA NASS) times share of N supplied by compound in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times mass compound per mass N in compound.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2022c) SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
