      <intermediateExchange id="9120975b-ce6f-567d-94e3-0d1a03bb87cc" unitId="86bbe475-8a8f-44d8-914c-e398787e7121" amount="0.000425410569020012" intermediateExchangeId="7225e2a6-7fd6-40e2-b341-f097b027d119" activityLinkId="c9e6a57e-3ae0-57ed-9914-50f1def85f20">
        <name xml:lang="en">application of plant protection product, by field sprayer</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">ha</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">6.00 ha/ha (4.25E-4 ha/kg Sweet Corn) application of plant protection product, by sprayer
Pesticide data is sometimes withheld in the NASS database to avoid disclosing data for individual operations (denoted with "D" in the data returned for the query, indicating a non-zero but withheld value). This is the case for almost all pesticide entries for sweet corn in Florida. Thus pesticide applications rates (quantity and compounds) are based on Clemson Extension (2020) data, which is consistent with the data presented in the Florida budgets (IFAS Extension 1999; IFAS Extension 2002; Virgina Cooperative Extension 2017). AIn the absence of data for acres treated the dataset assumes the guidance applies to all acres.  Application by sprayer accounts for 72% (3.25 passes) and aircraft for 28% (1.26 passes). FDACS (2022) Aerial Application of Seed, Pesticides and Fertilizer. Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services . https://www.fdacs.gov/Agriculture-Industry/Aerial-Application-of-Seed-Pesticides-and-Fertilizer
Field operations are as identified in crop- and rotation-specific enterprise crop budgets supplied by the regional agricultural extension office and matched to equipment type in the budget or crop guidance unless otherwise noted.  (Clemson Extension 2020, Kanissery et al 2022, Liu et al 2022b, Hanna, Mark 2016, Schuler and Frank 1998, Lattz and Schnitkey 2021b).  Operations are matched to equipment type and where multiple options are available, the share of each is determined from guidance and annual farmer survey data (Custom Rate Summaries) for contracted operations/equipment. 
Source(s): 
FDACS (2022) Aerial Application of Seed, Pesticides and Fertilizer. Florida Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services . https://www.fdacs.gov/Agriculture-Industry/Aerial-Application-of-Seed-Pesticides-and-Fertilizer; DeBruin J and Butzen S (2020) Nitrogen uptake by corn . Pioneer. https://www.pioneer.com/us/agronomy/nitrogen_uptake_corn.htmlaccessed 11-20-2021; NAAA (2020) Letter to the South Dakota Public Utilities Commission, July 30, 2020. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://puc.sd.gov/commission/dockets/electric/2021/EL21-018/prefiledexhibits/MBExhH.pdf; NAAA (2019) NAAA Member Survey Report. National Agricultural Aviation Association. https://www.agaviation.org/; Wilde M (2010) "Dusting crops a boon, necessity for farmers," in the WFC Courier, August 16, 2010.https://iowadot.gov/aviation/news/pdfs/Dusting%20crops%20a%20boonnecessity%20for%20farmers.pdf; FAA (2019) Table 5.1 - 2019 GENERAL AVIATION AND PART 135 TOTAL FUEL CONSUMED AND AVERAGE FUEL CONSUMPTION RATE BY AIRCRAFT TYPE, Table 3.2 - 2019 GENERAL AVIATION AND PART 135  TOTAL HOURS FLOWN BY ACTUAL USE BY AIRCRAFT TYPE. Federal Aviation Administration. https://www.faa.gov/data_research/aviation_data_statistics/general_aviation/CY2019/; Fritz B (2018) “Best Practices for Aerial Application” in EPA webinar series "Pesticide Spray Drift Series—3 Parts". USDA. https://www.epa.gov/sites/default/files/2019-04/documents/best-practices-for-aerial-application-slides.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021a) Machinery Cost Estimates: Summary. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/machinery-cost-estimates_summary.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021b) Machinery Cost Estimates: Field Operations. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/field_operations.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021c) Machinery Cost Estimates: Harvesting. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/harvest_operations_2021.pdf; Lattz and Schnitkey (2021d) Machinery Cost Estimates: Tractors. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/tractor_costs_2021.pdf; Swanson, Schnitkey, Paulson, Zulauf, Coppess (2020a) "Cost Management: Tillage Operations." farmdoc daily (10):151. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdocdaily.illinois.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/fdd180820.pdf; Swanson, Schnitkey, Paulson, Zulauf, Coppess (2020b) "Cost Management: Harvest Operations." farmdoc daily (10):158. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdocdaily.illinois.edu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/fdd010920.pdf; Kanissery et al. (2022) CHAPTER 17. SWEET CORN PRODUCTION. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv135; Liu et al (2022b) CHAPTER 2. FERTILIZER MANAGEMENT FOR VEGETABLE PRODUCTION IN FLORIDA. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv296; IPM (2002) Crop Profile for Corn (Sweet) in Florida. Integrated Pest Management. https://ipmdata.ipmcenters.org/documents/cropprofiles/FLSweetcorn2002.pdf;  () ; USDA NASS (2022c) SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC; Clemson Extension (2020) Sweetcorn - For roadside or local market. Cooperative Extension Service, Clemson University. , Kanissery et al. (2022) CHAPTER 17. SWEET CORN PRODUCTION. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv135, Liu et al (2022b) CHAPTER 2. FERTILIZER MANAGEMENT FOR VEGETABLE PRODUCTION IN FLORIDA. University of Florida's Institute of Food and Agricultural Sciences. https://edis.ifas.ufl.edu/publication/cv296, Hanna, Mark (2016) Estimating the Field Capacity of Farm Machines. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/pdf/a3-24.pdf, Schuler and Frank (1998) A3510 Estimating Agricultural Field Machinery Costs. University of Wisconsin-Extension. https://learningstore.uwex.edu/Assets/pdfs/A3510.pdf, Lattz and Schnitkey (2021b) Machinery Cost Estimates: Field Operations. Department of Agricultural and Consumer Economics, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. https://farmdoc.illinois.edu/assets/management/machinery-costs/field_operations.pdf</comment>
