        <name xml:lang="en">limestone, crushed, washed</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Application of limestone to raise soil pH, 232.39 kg/ha (1.65E-2 kg/kg Sweet Corn), calculated as the (mass of lime applied to treated acres (2 t/treated ha)) * fraction of crop area treated with lime (23.5%, from soil pH data from ) / (5  years between applications, based on Bly A and Gelderman R 2019). 
 Where other information is not available, the years between applications has been estimated as equivalent to or greater than the recommended re-test time.
