      <intermediateExchange id="5d10d3d4-c19e-56de-abff-e9293285a548" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.000785640710493186" intermediateExchangeId="cff23b42-5fa8-471b-b6fb-8a2cca249ca8" activityLinkId="1c608e58-eca0-5d8f-9e7a-424184718473">
        <name xml:lang="en">maize seed, for sowing</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Each planted hectare uses 11.08 kg seed (7.86E-4 kg/kg Sweet Corn). This value is calculated from a seeding rate of 69,189 seeds/ha (Graham, C. and G. Carlson 2016; Turnipseed, B 2016) and an average seed count of 6,244 seeds/kg (averaged from commercial listings of F1 (SH2 and se-se) seeds, https://www.ufseeds.com/vegetables/corn/supersweet-sh2-corn, https://lacrosseseed.com/product-information/forage-tech-sheets/tech-sheets-alfalfa-5). While genetically engineered sweet (fresh) corn seed is available, the share of sweet (fresh) corn grown from genetically engineered seed is not compiled; it is estimated that between 75 and 90% of North American sweet corn is conventional (USDA 2018b). Seeding rates are based on state average guidance, not specifically for GE or conventional seed.  Germination and stand losses are accounted for in the seeding rate.</comment>
