      <intermediateExchange id="6b5824c5-1830-5c91-89b5-81fd5801d1e7" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="007757-79-1" amount="0.00102881769510124" intermediateExchangeId="2f6880f1-d79c-436d-9fe2-5a589d0e504b" activityLinkId="f38ad6e0-ce17-56a0-a820-56ba5e3b795c">
        <name xml:lang="en">potassium nitrate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">1.03E-3 kg potassium nitrate/kg Sweet Corn. 
Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data N-P-K-S: 102.52--8.5--.3--2.97 kg/ha (USDA NASS data for 2018)Required nutrient met or exceeded by supply of required nitrogen using U.S. consumption mix. Quantity of specific fertiliser calculated from: average total N application (2018) reported cropped area of specified crop (conventional tillage) and share of compound in U.S. consumption mix (ecoinvent and IFA 2019) times each fertiliser's K2O to N ratio to deliver more than the necessary nutrient. The remaining K2O and S demands are met from a mix of ammonium sulfate, potassium nitrate, potassium chloride, and potassium sulfate, the quantities of which are determined by satisfying the demand without adding any additional excess of any nutrient beyond that resulting from assuming the U.S. average mix of N fertilizers; any S demand remaining is met using elemental sulfur.
Sources: 
USDA NASS (2022c) SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021. US Department of Agriculture (USDA) National Agricultural Statistics Service. https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC; Ecoinvent U.S. consumption mix for N fertilisers, from IFA data; IFA (2021) Nutrient content in percentage - IFA Fertilizer Converter. International Fertilizer Association. https://www.ifastat.org/converter/fertilizer-converter/accessed 2021-06-24</comment>
