      <elementaryExchange id="81831657-bffb-536b-8dfd-e5510b7c8673" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="016752-77-5" amount="1.93827814569536E-05" elementaryExchangeId="2bf4e40e-ed11-457a-ae60-53a5cc43fdc7" formula="C5H10N2O2S">
        <name xml:lang="en">Methomyl</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Methomyl emission to agricultural soil (2.734E-01 kg/ha).  Pesticides are assumed to be ultimately 100% emitted to soil across all rotation patterns, based on assumption that all sweet corn acres are treated, and assuming that cultivation is conventional tillage as common practice for weed management (EPA 2022; IPM 2003, IPM 1997).Data reported a quantity of total insecticides/herbicides/fungicides applied in sweet corn is sometimes available even when many of the substances in the category are reported with a “D”. If this total is available, the amount remaining after the sum of substance-specific values is accounted for is divided equally among the substances reported with a “D”. If the sum of available values exceeds or equals the total reported, any remaining “D” substances are treated as zero and omitted.  
Sources: SWEETCORN - APPLICATIONS, MEASURED IN LB / ACRE / YEAR, AVG (fertilizer and pesticides, amount, number of applications) - 2000-2021,https://quickstats.nass.usda.gov/#5E5B411A-F9EF-3B83-AAFF-995DD89820FC,IPM center (1997) Crop Profile for Corn (Sweet) in Maryland. Southern Integrated Pest Management Center. https://ipmdata.ipmcenters.org/documents/cropprofiles/MDcorn-sweet.pdf,IPM center (2003) Crop Profile for Sweet Corn in the North Central United States. Southern Integrated Pest Management Center.Southern Integrated Pest Management Center. https://ipmdata.ipmcenters.org/documents/cropprofiles/us-ncr-sweetcorn.pdf ,EPA (2022) Assessment of the Benefits of Atrazine and the Impacts of Potential Mitigation for Field Corn, Sweet Corn, Sorghum, and Sugarcane; PC Code (080803). (MEMORANDUM).US Environmental Protection Agency. https://downloads.regulations.gov/EPA-HQ-OPP-2013-0266-1624/content.pdf</comment>
