      <elementaryExchange id="146719aa-4f4a-5a83-8bcd-764abbc61799" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" casNumber="014797-55-8" amount="0.0108983903308361" elementaryExchangeId="b9291c72-4b1d-4275-8068-4c707dc3ce33" formula="NO3-">
        <name xml:lang="en">Nitrate</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">The total nitrate leaching/runoff is 1.676E+2 kg NO3/ha (1.090E-2kg NO3/kg Sweet Corn), 7.770E+1 kg NO3/ha from fertilisers, 0.000E+0 kg NO3/ha 0, 9.460E+1 kg NO3/ha from soil mineralization, and -4.746E+0 kg NO3 N uptake. 
8.3% is emitted to surface water and 91.7% to ground water, since 8.3% of cropland in Florida has drainage (ISU Extension 2020c).
Nitrate leaching is calculated with the SQCB-NO3 model (Faist Emmenegger et al. 2009) using general (state-level parameters for slope and clay content, local precipitation and irrigation data). 
Sources: 
Faist Emmenegger M, Reinhard J, Zah R (2009) Sustainability Quick Check for Biofuels - in- termediate background report. With contributions from T. Ziep, R. Weichbrodt, Prof. Dr. V. Wohlgemuth, FHTW Berlin and A. Roches, R. Freiermuth Knuchel, Dr. G. Gaillard, Agroscope Reckenholz-Tänikon. Dübendorf. https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Rainer-Zah/publication/230725635_SQCB_-_Sustainability_Quick_Check_for_Biofuels_Second_draft_18th_February_2009_-_Intermediate_Background_Report_With_contributions_from_T_Ziep_R_Weichbrodt_Prof_Dr_V_Wohlgemuth_FHTW_Berlin_and_A_Roche/links/56b458fb08ae1f8aa45392e6/SQCB-Sustainability-Quick-Check-for-Biofuels-Second-draft-18th-February-2009-Intermediate-Background-Report-With-contributions-from-T-Ziep-R-Weichbrodt-Prof-Dr-V-Wohlgemuth-FHTW-Berlin-and-A-R.pdf; DeBruin J and Butzen S (2020) Nitrogen uptake by corn . Pioneer. https://www.pioneer.com/us/agronomy/nitrogen_uptake_corn.htmlaccessed 11-20-2021; Fan, Y., Wang, Z., Liao, D. et al. Uptake and utilization of nitrogen, phosphorus and potassium as related to yield advantage in maize-soybean intercropping under different row configurations. Sci Rep 10, 9504 (2020). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-020-66459-y; Hollinger S E (1995) Midwestern Climate Center Soils Atlas and Database. Crop Science Extension &amp; Outreach, University of Illinois .  https://www.isws.illinois.edu/pubdoc/C/ISWSC-179.pdf; Bruulsema T and Jones J D (2021) Soil Test Summary 2020. Foundation for Agronomic Research and Plant Nutrition Canada present this 2020 summary of soil test levels in North America. Foundation for Agronomic Research, Plant Nutrition Canada. https://soiltest.tfi.org/about/about_soil_test_summaryaccessed August 30, 2021
ISU Extension (2020c) Crop Production Costs Budget - Corn following Soybeans. Cooperative Extension Service, Iowa State University of Science and Technology. https://www.extension.iastate.edu/agdm/crops/xls/a1-20cfs_tbl2.xlsx</comment>
