        <name xml:lang="en">Occupation, annual crop, irrigated</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m2*year</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Land occupation per year (annual growing season).  Land is under rotation with other annual crop production (~80% corn-soy, ~20% corn-corn, Socolar et al 2021). US NRCS data indicates that land is leaving agricultural production rather than being transitioned into it, thus the continuous flux to/from annual crop is effectively steady state. Annual production averaged  0.7  million tonnes from  2016-2021 on . million ha planted and . million ha harvested. Thus occupation is 0.428 ha/t or 4282.466 m2/t (0.4.282m2/kg). This overall land use is split into irrigated ( 86.64% ) and non-irrigated ( 13.4% ) based on agricultural census data ( USDA NASS ) 3.71E-1 m2 planted/kg harvested maize of irrigated land, and 5.72E-2 m2 planted/kg harvested maize of non-irrigated land</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.401963427928402" mu="-0.9113941698041024" variance="0.002" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.0029"/>
